<br>
In brief, I've met Lemeth and a few others.  Montagor is from Erudin and not actually blood related to the family, but he *was* related through marriage.  Montagor fell in love with and married a heretic, only to return home with his new bride to find that his family wanted nothing to do with either of them.<br>
<br>
A noble son of a family of spellcasters by birth, Montagor found himself alone and penniless, and also without the love of his life by his side any longer.  Meralith (Montagor's wife/lover) commit suicide the night they came into Erudin.  She didn't want to take Montagor's family from him.<br>
<br>
Since Montagor's own family will have nothing to do with him, even after the tragedy, Montagor returned to Paineel where he spent some time with &quot;in-laws&quot; for lack of a better term.  An agnostic by faith, his belief in Order is quickly being shaken up... (what alignment choices do Erudite magicians get at level 10, again? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
Since there has never been a funeral for Meralith, that might be an interesting event that would drag both sides of the family together.  Some of the residents of Erudin might even be looking for Montagor, since he disappeared and has not had contact with his family in months.<br>
<br>
Montagor was last seen near Qeynos, disgusted with his own people.  Rumor has it that he has taken up with a band of druids and rangers in the area, and this group works to keep the Qeynos Hills area safe for travelers.<br>
<br>
